<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,639,778,1729]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,280,991,1012]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Broun, 1893 b:" authorityYear="1050" box="[463,535,1018,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtalis">
<emphasis box="[463,535,1018,1039]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">hirtalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the following combination of characters: antennomere 1 elongate, approximately 3 times longer than wide; antennomere 4 elongate; posterior frontal fovea elongate; eye small, one-third length of temple; hind wings well-developed; shape of genitalia unique to species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,639,778,1729]" lastBlockId="13.[685,1172,194,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,386,1204,1225]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Length 3.0 mm. Body brown and elytra, legs, maxillary palpi yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[229,303,1257,1278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,386,1257,1278]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Head:</emphasis>
As long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[286,362,1283,1304]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 3 times longer than wide, 2–3 longer than wide, 4 elongate, approximately 1.5 times longer than wide, 5 longer than wide, 6–10 subquadrate. Frontal sulcus deep and reaching behind eye from end of frontal rostral lobes. Anterior frontal fovea round, posterior frontal fovea elongate. Eye small and prominent, one-third length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,637,1469,1490]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at one-third length. Elytra rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[425,499,1522,1543]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Hind wings well-developed. Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[329,435,1575,1596]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergite IV with pair of transverse patches of microtrichia reaching middle. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[242,356,1629,1650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe longer than parameres with semicircular apical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[555,627,1655,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
). Phallobase of median lobe asymmetrical and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[244,322,1708,1729]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
). Right paramere divided into 2 branches from base, and minor branch divided into 2 long branches (
<figureCitation box="[903,974,221,242]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
